@FONT helvetica.font 13
@SMARTWRAP

@NODE MAIN "ImageEditor - Macro: multiple ShapeMasks [Freeware]"
@TOC "Macros.guide/MAIN"

@{LINDENT 4}
@{PAR}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}multiple ShapeMasks@{UB}@{FG TEXT}@{LINE}
@{PAR}@{B}Creating multiple Shape Masks & Shadow.@{UB}@{LINE}
@{PAR}Reads a portable anymap as input.
Writes out an antialiased sharp Mask (GREY), a soft Mask (GREY) and a shadow Image (COLOR).@{LINE}
The output dimensions depends on the source Image size.
The sharp Mask and shadow Image size is a few pixels greater then the source Image.
To get fine results, the source Images background color shoul'd be white.@{LINE}
@{PAR}@{B}1.2@{UB} (26.10.2000)  @{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{I}(c) 2000 by Christian Effenberger @{UI}@{FG TEXT}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE
